tingale/OptionalStopping.html#MeasureTheory.submartingale_of_expected_stoppedValue_mono\"><span class=\"name\">MeasureTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">submartingale_of_expected_stoppedValue_mono</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">Ω</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">m0</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/MeasurableSpace/Defs.html#MeasurableSpace\">MeasurableSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">Ω</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">μ</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.Measure\">Measure</a> <span class=\"fn\">Ω</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">𝒢</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Process/Filtration.html#MeasureTheory.Filtration\">Filtration</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a> <span class=\"fn\">m0</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">Ω</span> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a></span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Process/Filtration.html#MeasureTheory.SigmaFiniteFiltration\">SigmaFiniteFiltration</a> <span class=\"fn\">μ</span> <span class=\"fn\">𝒢</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hadp</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Process/Adapted.html#MeasureTheory.StronglyAdapted\">StronglyAdapted</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝒢</span> <span class=\"fn\">f</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hint</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Function/L1Space/Integrable.html#MeasureTheory.Integrable\">Integrable</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">μ</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hf</span> :\n  <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">τ </span><span class=\"fn\">π</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">Ω</span> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/ENat/Defs.html#ENat\">ℕ∞</a></span>),\n    <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Process/Stopping.html#MeasureTheory.IsStoppingTime\">IsStoppingTime</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝒢</span> <span class=\"fn\">τ</span></span> →\n      <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Process/Stopping.html#MeasureTheory.IsStoppingTime\">IsStoppingTime</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝒢</span> <span class=\"fn\">π</span></span> →\n        <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">τ</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">π</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(∃ (<span class=\"fn\">N</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>), <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">ω</span> : <span class=\"fn\">Ω</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">π</span> <span class=\"fn\">ω</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">N</span></span></span>)</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Bochner/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.integral\">∫</a> (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">Ω</span>)<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Bochner/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.integral\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Process/Stopping.html#MeasureTheory.stoppedValue\">stoppedValue</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">τ</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Bochner/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.integral\">∂</a><span class=\"fn\">μ</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Bochner/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.integral\">∫</a> (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">Ω</span>)<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Bochner/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.integral\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Process/Stopping.html#MeasureTheory.stoppedValue\">stoppedValue</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">π</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Integral/Bochner/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.integral\">∂</a><span class=\"fn\">μ</span></span></span></span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Martingale/Basic.html#MeasureTheory.Submartingale\">Submartingale</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">𝒢</span> <span class=\"fn\">μ</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The converse direction of the optional stopping theorem, i.e. a strongly adapted integrable\nprocess `f` is a submartingale if for all bounded stopping times `τ` and `π` such that `τ ≤ π`, the\nstopped value of `f` at `τ` has expectation smaller than its stopped value at `π`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Probability/Martingale/OptionalStopping.html#MeasureTheory.submartingale_of_expected_stoppedValue_mono","kind":"theorem","line":70,"name":"MeasureTheory.submartingale_of_expected_stoppedValue_mono","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7